n><hr size=1> This seems to happen a lot. On a raid, a shaman (usually 60 w/ torpor) will ask for mod rods, rod himself down, then ask a druid to heal him (time was not an issue). I was simply stupidfied at this shamans request. Am I correct in assuming that shamans have a spell called caniblize which will take HPs and convert them into mana in the same fassion as a mod rod? and once they mod their health down, can't they heal themselves? Don't they have a spell called torpor that will heal them very nicely for a low cost of mana? I think they do, actually. So what the hell? are shamans (at least the ones I know) too lazy to do all that work? would they rather rely on the abilities of other classes to do something themselves can do? Why the hell are they asking me to heal them? Is my mana not as important as a shamans? that's the feeling I'm getting. This also happens a lot in experiance groups. A shaman will cani himself down, then ask a druid to heal him. Why can't he heal himself? Again, I am getting the feeling that shamans seem to think druid mana is not as important as a shamans. Can anyone identify with me? or explain why shamans ask for this? Maybe I'm not seeing something here. <p><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD>
<A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=80 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame/9.png" ALT="What Video Game Character Are You? I am Kong." /></A>I am <B>Kong</B>.<BR /><BR />
Strong and passionate, I tend to be misunderstood, sometimes even feared. I don't want to fight, I don't want to cause trouble, all I ask is a little love, and a little peace. If I don't get what I want, I get angry, and throw barrels and flaming oil at whatever's stopping me.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=189459>My Magelo profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluviane01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luviane01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 6:57:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shamans, the druid's drunken half brother.</span><hr size=1> I play a druid, my husband plays a shaman.  Before he cannablizes, he asks me for Regrowth.  A high level shaman usually has to buff quite a few people, with 3 or 4 buffs a piece.  I prefer to handle the shaman's healing needs, thus saving the cleric's mana for what he/she needs it for.  Some of the shaman's buffs take 1 blue bubble of mana for one cast.  After they've done buffing, they're usually on debuff duty such as slows, or dot's.  So, it's kind of important that they get their mana back as quickly as possible.  Assuming the shaman doesn't have clarity or KEI, who wants to wait the 15 minutes it takes him to med up to full?  Hope this helps?<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp  =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br>  Posts: 1113<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 8:16:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/aidon60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shamans, the druid's drunken half brother.</span><hr size=1> Generally its a speed thing even if its not an issue.  Torpor is great for maintaining mana, but if you just buffed an entire raid and are OOM, you Canni down then if you use torpor, you have to wait 24 seconds before its done healing and then you have recast time etc etc.  Its faster to get from OOM to FM to canni all the way down and have someone with direct heals heal you back up so you can keep canni'ing down <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24579">Aidon</a>
<br>
Leader of the Bitter Druids
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukildaerelisiofra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kildaere LiSiofra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.animationlibrary.com/Animation11/Webdesign_Elements/Bullets/rotor1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 8:38:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.marua.com/lily/seraphim/av_shion_04.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shamans, the druid's drunken half brother.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> A shaman will cani himself down, then ask a druid to heal him. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I usually OFFER to heal shamans while they canni, 4 good chloro's and they are full hps, at the expense of 2 nukes worth of my mana. Shaman buffs &gt; Girdle, hun, and they slow and haste as well. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Why can't he heal himself? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Isn't that kinda like doing something for nothing? Chewing on his arm to get enough mana to heal himself for the damage he took chewing on his arm?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Again, I am getting the feeling that shamans seem to think druid mana is not as important as a shamans. Can anyone identify with me? or explain why shamans ask for this? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->While you are under the impression that they are thinking thier mana is more important than yours, I am thinking they do 3 times the work that I do in a group, using more than 4 times the mana I do. Ehh, it all balances out. <br>
 <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=136857><font size="-5" face="Tahoma" color=#333399>Baroness Kildaere Li'Siofra</a><br>Hierophant<br><a href=http://www.guardiansofvalour.com>Guardians of Valour</a><font size="-8" face="Tahoma" color=#333399><br>Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fyyrlustorm>FyyrLuStorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Small Pissed Off Diety<br>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 9:20:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> That is what is called Druid Twitching.<br>
<br>
I wont do it for anyone other than Clerics though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=araxx>Araxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Might be Housebroken</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 10:40:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> If on a raid, and it'll speed things up and makes things go faster it is actually very efficient. It is not degrading  though. At least not from my point of view. It is something that needs to be done to get the whole raid going. Hell, Clerics have to heal those tanks because they stand and hit that uber mob. Shamans mega buff those Tanks so they are more effective, and we keep the shaman's mana pool kinda full so they can do some more magic to make the monsters hit less. It is a role I don't like much, but I've only had to do it a few times. And it helps.<br>
<br>
Take it from this perspective: If you have to heal a Tank for doing his job, what is the difference if you have to heal a Shaman for doing his? There is none.<br>
<br>
Ciao for now!<br>
<br>
 <p>Araxx Darkroot - 57 Preserver<br>
Clan of the Roc<br>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>Penguin WRAA!</b><br>Assistant Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 894<br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/02 11:07:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=714.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/temp/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shamans, the druid's drunken half brother.</span><hr size=1> Name:  Khura's Focusing <br>
Level:  60 <br>
Mana:  1250 <br>
<br>
Name:  Talisman of the Brute <br>
Level:  57 <br>
Mana:  350 <br>
<br>
