Effects: Target: Regenerate Health (1200) <br>
  Target: Slow Attack Rate (30%) <br>
  Target: Snare <br>
  Target: Reduce Mana (50) <br>
<br>
So, assuming that a shaman can Can4 four times before Torpor runs out, he's recovered 168 points of mana (not counting standing regen, c3, etc).  He should be full health because he's recovered 700 more hp than he needed.<br>
<br>
Now, assuming that you have a smart shaman who's cast Can4 at least 8 times, he can then hit torpor to get back to full health.  At that point, he's recovered 656 mana, then you subtract 200 mana for torpor, for a net recovered amount of 456 mana over about a minute.  At that rate, the shaman will be able to cast <b>one</b> group focus in 2.5 to 3 minutes.<br>
<br>
So, assuming that your clerics are casting:<br>
Name:  Blessing of Aegolism <br>
Level:  60 <br>
Mana:  2000 <br>
And that clerics have no natural way of recovering mana, other than to med, yes, your mana is less important in a raid. <p><center>
